      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Do not give aspirin to a child under 18, as it can cause a serious condition called Reye's syndrome. For fever relief in an 8-year-old, you should use children's acetaminophen (Tylenol) or ibuprofen (Motrin/Advil), following the dosing instructions on the bottle. If the fever is very high or he seems severely ill, it is best to call your pediatrician right away.",
